<br>
If it is based on the latter (helpfulness to group) and assuming you guys want to be a fairly self-sufficient group, it looks to me as if you would want to create one of the healing classes: a cleric, druid or shaman.  Without a healer you won't be able to do a lot of things if it is just the three of you.  However, I feel you should create the character you want to play and let the chips fall where they may be.  That way you will make new buddies outside your threesome and expand your options.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukisarintenamin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KisarinTenamin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 3:34:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1546.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping Question</span><hr size=1> I see two barriers to your grouping together.<br>
<br>
First is the alignment issue.  Since the Wiz is Erudite, I am assuming thathe monks are in Qeynos.  This makes the Monks Neutral to start, but I don't know about the Erudite.  Have him/her type /alignment when in game.  It it says she is good you will not be able to group with the Iksar.  If I am wrong and the monks are from Freeport, you will not abe able to group until level 10 when you can change their alignment.  The issue is that the Iksar is evil and will never be anything but evil.  The other characters will have to adapt.<br>
<br>
The Second issue is just simply that the Iksar don't have good means to get to travel.  You may not be able to get your Iksar to the same zone as your other characters until around level 10-15 (and even then it may be tough).  You don't have realistic access to the Nexus until late 20s and maybe not even until mid 30s.  If you take the boat (a long run to get there past dangerous mobs) use the one in Overthere, and then you have to run all the way there (more deadly zones) and some how sneak your way past the guards in Highpass (impossible unless you can get an invis) or Rivervale (even harder) then past more deadly zones to get to Qeynos where you will HAVE to get a bind before you kill one thing because you don't want to have to run that lenght again.  Also training will be a major thing, and monks are one of the classes that need to visit their trainer at least ever 4th level as I recall.  You will have to go all the way back to Cabilis to find a trainer.<br>
<br>
<br>
Judging by your questions, I am assuming that you are a new player, I don't reccomend starting with an Iksar if you are because they are KOS (Kill On Sight) in any other town on Norrath.  Monks are decent starting characters, but not the Iksar monks.  If you are looking for something different, checkout the Barbarian Beastlord.  That will be near Qeynos (and a do able run if you are real careful and catch Blackburrow at a busy time.) and give you a different character that is both challenging and relatively easy to play (pets make for challenges and easy getaways).<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts<br>
<br>
Tenamin Kor 30singer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ueliezeroferudin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezer of Erudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 368<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 3:54:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1546.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Grouping Question</span><hr size=1> One thing to note about Erudite Wizards and Alignment.  If you choose to worship Solusek Ro, Patron of Wizards, you have very restrictive alignment choices.  You will start Neutral Good, and your ONLY option to change to is Neutral Evil.<br>
<br>
If you choose a different Deity or be Agnostic you can be Order Neutral.<br>
<br>
The reason Sol Ro Erudite Wizards get such an odd track is because Erudites can NOT be Disorder and Sol Ro worshippers can NOT be Order.  I guess one or the other disallows Neutral as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1546.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1546.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1546.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=1546.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1546.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1546.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="firionaviefrm1">Firiona Vie General Chat<option value="firionaviefrm2">The Market Square<option value="firionaviefrm4">The Soapbox<option value="firionaviefrm6">Signature Testing<option value="firionaviefrm7">Patch Messages<option value="firionaviefrm8">RP Server Rules<option value="firionaviefrm9">OT/OO